                            <comment id="13211821" author="udachny" created="Mon, 20 Feb 2012 12:53:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Answering your question .. I kept the superclass only for backward compatibility purposes. I doubt anyone is using it in production.&lt;br/&gt;
Just in case it is used somewhere in experimental environment, it will keep working. If you find it is not useful any more, I can eliminate it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13212007" author="srowen" created="Mon, 20 Feb 2012 17:56:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you are willing and interested you are welcome to remov the super class. I dont think we must retain it at this stage. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13219927" author="udachny" created="Thu, 1 Mar 2012 08:50:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just realized that if I to remove the superclass, you&apos;d have to rewrite chapter 5.4 of &quot;Mahout in Action&quot;. It references &lt;em&gt;PlusAnonymousUserDataModel&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
